<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JAN 93 / World Stock Markets: Brazil
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
SAO PAULO'S Bovespa index rallied from an early afternoon low, but was still
off 1.3 per cent, or 1,164 points, at 87,833 at the close. At worst it was
down some 4 per cent. Brokers said that investors were anxious over the
Brazilian senate's vote today on a long-delayed port bill, which will
propose the privatisation of services and deregulation of the labour market.
