   SAN FRANCISCO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
CYPRESS Semiconductor recorded a net loss for its fourth quarter and year
after restructuring charges. Fourth-quarter sales were down 5 per cent as
prices for the Silicon Valley chipmaker's main products came under pressure,
writes Louise Kehoe in San Francisco.
