<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JAN 93 / Pilkington prices to increase 8%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
PILKINGTON, the glass group, has told UK customers that its prices will rise
8 per cent from February 1. Its glass is used by the motor and construction
industries.
Glass prices have fallen sharply through the recession, and with volumes
declining as well, Pilkington's UK operations fell into loss. UK float glass
prices have fallen more than 20 per cent since September 1990 and last
summer the group cut its dividend.
Previous attempts to increase prices failed as imports undercut Pilkington.
Following the fall in sterling last autumn, however, Pilkington has started
to rebuild market share in the UK and is now more optimistic that a price
rise will hold.
Pilkington shares rose 4p to 111p yesterday.
</TEXT>
