<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JAN 93 / Labour urged to make corporate deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL CASSELL, Business Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Labour party should take advantage of the new relationship emerging
between government and business and strike a 'socialist deal' with the
corporate sector, says a paper published today by the Institute for Public
Policy Research, the leftwing think tank.
Written by Mr Roger Warren Evans, regional property director for the J.
Sainsbury supermarket chain, the paper says the consumer society has shifted
power decisively towards the corporate sector while the process of
globalisation has drained it away from national governments.
The task for Labour, he says, is to reach a mutually beneficial
understanding with managers who have been alienated from governments of the
Thatcher era which refused to plan long-term investment.
Coming to Terms. IPPR, 30-32 Southampton St, London WC1E 7RA. Pounds 2 95.
