<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JAN 93 / Reserve Bank of India announces loans package
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By R C MURTHY
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BOMBAY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Reserve Bank of India, the country's central bank, yesterday announced
an Rs10bn (Pounds 226m) loans package to promote growth, R C Murthy reports
from Bombay. The bank is channelling loans worth Rs4bn to farming, mainly
for machinery, and Rs6bn for purchases of heavy vehicles to ease a slump in
engineering. While the bank expects overall economic growth to reach about 4
per cent in the year to June 1993, it is worried this relies heavily on
exceptional expansion in agriculture, while other industry remains stagnant.
</TEXT>
