</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER PEARSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
JAMES CREAN has spent Dollars 5.5m, or Pounds 3.61m, to acquire the 50 per
cent of Valley Fresh Foods, of Turlock, California, that it did not already
own and over which it had an option.
The Dublin-based food, household goods and industrial equipment wholesaler
bought its original 50 per cent holding in Valley Fresh in 1990.
