branded chicken products had been 'very satisfactory' and that as a result
it had decided to exercise its option to buy the balance.
In the 1991 year Crean lifted turnover to IPounds 208.7m (IPounds 179.7m),
though pre-tax profits declined by more than IPounds 1m to IPounds 18.5m, or
Pounds 16.9m.
However, it said at the time of the results that the comparisons were skewed
by the investments in Valley Fresh and Egidius Janssen in the Netherlands in
1990 and by the consolidation of Valley Fresh's results into the 1991
accounts.
